    "summary": "AREAS of INTEREST: urban planning, public policy, urban public space, mobility, circularity, degrowth, well-being and quality of life, health and nature, attitudes and behavioral change, public participation, responsible education.\n\n#  Advisor and Consultant.\nProject Management: Advising governments, housing corporations and developers on the implementation of urban and infrastructural projects to ensure and enhance smooth project implementation. \nPolicy design: Advising governments, NGO and businesses delivering thorough contents and actionable insights based on primary and secondary research on a variety of topics aiming at creating a more livable, responsible and equal societies.\nI provide report, articles, infographics and ghostwriting services to disseminate knowledge to all kind of public.\n\n# Researcher. \nI investigate how the science of well-being helps improving urban livability, developing responsible societies, and fostering human flourishing. I apply interdisciplinary and mixed-method approaches primarily mastering qualitative analyses but also quantitative and geospatial techniques.\nPublication productivity, conferences, fieldwork, data collection, collaborative projects within communities and public sectors as well as with businesses and stakeholders that aspire to increase sustainability, social impact and innovation. \n\n# Founder & Director - Educational Foundation - volunteer.\nIn 2016 I founded a project offering social opportunities and educational activities for Italian-speaking kids. Now I lead the development towards what\u2019s currently a foundation with a staff of 15 creative women and volunteers that offer regular activities throughout the whole school year.\nI professionally grew while boosting and loving this project and I\u2019ve acquired skills in community building and engagement, team facilitator, active learning processes, responsible education, cultural diversity, communication, public speaking, product management, budgeting, brand identity, business development, and stakeholders management.",
